:"Note that timeout functions may be delayed, due to the processing of other","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"event sources. Thus they should not be relied on for precise timing."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"After each call to the timeout function, the time of the next"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"timeout is recalculated based on the current time and the given interval","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(it does not try to ‘catch up’ time lost in delays)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"main-loop.html#memory-management-of-sources","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for details"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on how to handle the return value and memory management of "},{"code":"data","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This internally creates a main loop source using"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.timeout_source_new","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and attaches it to the global"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"] using [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.Source.attach","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"], so the callback"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will be invoked in whichever thread is running that main context. You can do","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"these steps manually if you need greater control or to use a custom main","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"context.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The interval given is in terms of monotonic time, not wall clock time."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"See [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.get_monotonic_time","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/timeoutAddFull(priority:interval:function:data:notify:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/sourceRemove":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"sourceRemove"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s5Int32V","text":"Int32","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceRemove","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourceremove","abstract":[{"text":"Use this macro as the return value of a [callback","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFunc","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] to remove"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the [struct"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source"},{"type":"text","text":"] from the main loop."}],"title":"sourceRemove"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContext"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"title":"MainContext","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}]},"main-loop.html#memory-management-of-sources":{"url":"main-loop.html#memory-management-of-sources","title":"main loop memory management","type":"link","identi